(In reply to Tomoaki AOKI from comment #49)
Why, why, WHY you have to copy repo use and use third-party tool instead of native pkg ability while you already have a valid repo in poudriere?


# cat > /usr/local/etc/pkg/repos/local.conf <<EOF
local: {
  url: "file:///usr/local/poudriere/data/packages/${ABI}"
}
EOF

# cat > /usr/local/etc/pkg/repos/FreeBSD.conf <<EOF
FreeBSD: {
  enabled: NO
}
EOF
